\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Skip to 2 minutes and 39 seconds\cb1 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
\cf4 Most of these patterns were caused by a bad measurement processes that involved kids being kids. We know that there are a lot of things wrong with this data because we know a lot about arm spans, heights, and children. But if we were investigating something we knew almost nothing about, we'd probably have no idea that we were looking at artefacts, rather than facts, aspects of the real relationship. Lessons. Artefacts are artificial patterns caused by deficiencies in the data collection process. No data collection processes are ever perfect, so in data analysis we're always struggling to distinguish between facts and artefacts. Artefacts can be quite persuasive, especially when delivered in proficiently presented graphics.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight/8/steps/508372#"}}{\fldrslt 
