\cf4 This is a big problem with many data streams sourced from the internet, where no one knows what sorts of biassing filtering processes have affected what data ended up getting recorded and stored. Data goes bad from two main causes. Bad measurement processes, measurements that do not actually measure what they are meant to, and bias, the process by which some things get recorded while others don't, can cause systematic biases. Additionally, all sorts of things can go wrong when data is being entered and moved around on computers. Real data is also full of holes, values that are missing for various reasons.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
