\cf4 If the people we have values for tend to be different from those whose values have gone missing, then we automatically have bias. But why is all this so important? Garbage in, garbage out. Unfortunately, we may not always recognise when our data is garbage. When the data's in, it is too late to do anything about it. The best protection against bad data is to design good data collection processes at the outset. That is before the data is collected. This brings us to the end of this video. Next time we'll talk about the problems in determining cause and effect.\
